properties.headline: Wind Chill Warning issued February 4 at 8:09PM MST until February 5 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...BLOWING AND DRIFTING SNOW ALONG WITH EXTREME WINDCHILLS
POSSIBLE TONIGHT ACROSS THE WIND PRONE AREAS OF INTERSTATE 80
WITH HEAVY MOUNTAIN SNOW LATER IN THE WEEK...

* WHAT...Dangerously cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as
low as 45 below zero.

* WHERE...Interior valleys of Carbon and Albany Counties in
Wyoming.

* WHEN...Until 8 AM MST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause frostbite
on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes. Move animals to
shelter and avoid excessive outdoor exposure until temperatures
warm.
properties.instruction:
Avoid outside activities if possible. When outside, make sure you
wear appropriate clothing, a hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM MST WEDNESDAY
